108"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CAR", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9939127564430237, "span": {"begin": 705, "end": 708}}, {"id": ["mesh:D010634"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "phenobarbital", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.998100221157074, "span": {"begin": 728, "end": 741}}, {"id": ["mesh:C028474"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "TCPOBOP", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9976045489311218, "span": {"begin": 746, "end": 753}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:846", "9970", "5573", "1525", "6687", "10206", "653108"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "CAR activators", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.7832279205322266, "span": {"begin": 1060, "end": 1074}}, {"id": ["mesh:D011230"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "pre-neoplastic", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9799656271934509, "span": {"begin": 1101, "end": 1115}}], "text": "The observed increase in numbers of preneoplastic foci, usually with eosinophilic staining properties, is observed with great regularity in mode of action work of CAR activating xenobiotics where histopathology at later times has been examined. This increase in foci (mixed or eosinophilic) after 2 years was observed at tumorigenic dose levels with metofluthrin in male rats (Deguchi et al., 2009), and at tumorigenic dose levels in mice treated with phenobarbital (Jones et al., 2009). With TCPOBOP in mice, multiple eosinophilic foci were reported to co-occur along with an increased incidence of eosinophilic adenomas and carcinomas after 60 weeks of treatment (Diwan et al., 1992). With well-studied CAR activators such as phenobarbital and TCPOBOP, increased cell proliferation has&nbsp;been detected at similar dose levels where increased altered foci are seen (Geter et al., 2014; Huang et al., 2005; Kolaja et al., 1996a; Kolaja et al., 1996b) (Tables 2&nbsp;and 3); therefore, there is strong support for the linkage of these earlier key events with CAR activators leading to an increase in pre-neoplastic foci.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:49:09 +0000 2026"}